<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN332">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>piṟarvēl pōlā tāki yivvūr</l>
<l>maṟavaṉ vēlō peruntakai yuṭaittē</l>
<l>yirumpuṟa nīṟu māṭik kalantiṭaik</l>
<l>kurampaik kūraik kiṭakkiṉuṅ kiṭakku</l>
<l>maṅkala makaḷiroṭu mālai cūṭṭi</l>
<l>yiṉkura lirumpai yāḻoṭu tatumpat</l>
<l>teṇṇīrp paṭuviṉun teruviṉun tirintu</l>
<l>maṇmuḻu taḻuṅkac celliṉuñ cellumāṅ</l>
<l>kiruṅkaṭaṟ ṟāṉai vēntar</l>
<l>peruṅkaḷiṟṟu mukattiṉuñ celavā ṉātē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Being unlike the spears of others, as for the spear </l>
<l>of the bold man from this village, it possesses great befittingness. (1f.)</l>
<l>Bathing [its] large back in ashes(?), mingling in between, (3)</l>
<l>even if it lies, it will lie under the roof of a hut, (4)</l>
<l>and, being adorned with garlands by auspicious women, (5)</l>
<l>while sweet voices resound along with the lute in a large bag, (6)</l>
<l>wandering from clear-watered wells to streets, (7)</l>
<l>even if it goes it will go so that the whole earth is laid waste, and thus (8)</l>
<l>it won’t end in going into the face of the large elephant bull (10)</l>
<l>of kings with armies [like] the vast ocean. (9)   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
